message.content:
Below is one systematic way to interpret and build the two “towers” shown in your target photo.  The left‐hand tower uses four blocks, and the right‐hand tower uses five, all drawn from the dictionary without reorienting any piece.

────────────────────────────────────────
1)  Analysis of the Main Target Image
────────────────────────────────────────
•  The structure actually consists of two separate “towers.”  
•  Left Tower (3 layers, 4 blocks total):  
   –  Bottom Layer: one small green cube (left) and one small blue cube (right).  
   –  Middle Layer: one red “C‐shaped” block with its semicircle facing outward.  
   –  Top Layer: one green rectangular “beam” laid horizontally.  

•  Right Tower (4 layers, 5 blocks total):  
   –  Bottom Layer: two identical red “U‐shaped” blocks side by side (arches facing up).  
   –  Second Layer: one blue cube on top of the red arches.  
   –  Third Layer: one green rectangular “beam” laid horizontally.  
   –  Top Layer: one orange wedge forming the “roof.”  

Altogether, there are 9 blocks used in the photo.

────────────────────────────────────────
2)  Selecting the Needed Dictionary Blocks
────────────────────────────────────────
Matching each colored shape and orientation in the target gives:

•  Left Tower  
   1.  Green cube  →  Block #5  
   2.  Blue cube   →  Block #4  
   3.  Red “C”     →  Block #3 (curved opening facing front, as shown)  
   4.  Green beam  →  Block #8 (horizontal rectangle)  

•  Right Tower  
   5.  Red “U”     →  Block #2 (used twice to make the base)  
   6.  Blue cube   →  Block #4 (used again)  
   7.  Green beam  →  Block #8 (used again)  
   8.  Orange wedge  →  Block #15  

Hence the required indices (with repeats) are:
[#2, #2, #3, #4, #4, #5, #8, #8, #15].

────────────────────────────────────────
3)  Suggested Assembly Order
────────────────────────────────────────
A convenient bottom‐to‐top build sequence is:

{
  Step1: Move block with index 5      // Left tower bottom (green cube)
  Step2: Move block with index 4      // Left tower bottom (blue cube)
  Step3: Move block with index 3      // Place red "C" on top
  Step4: Move block with index 8      // Cap left tower with green beam
  Step5: Move block with index 2      // Right tower base, first red "U"
  Step6: Move block with index 2      // Right tower base, second red "U"
  Step7: Move block with index 4      // Blue cube atop the red arches
  Step8: Move block with index 8      // Green beam above the blue cube
  Step9: Move block with index 15     // Orange wedge on top
}

Following these nine steps with the blocks exactly as pictured in the dictionary (no further rotation) reproduces the target arrangement.
